@node RX_WDIMS "TTManager ARexx:  GetWindowDims & SetWindowDims"
@toc AREXX

@{u}@{b}GetWindowDims@{ub}@{uu}
  Returns window position and dimension data.


@{b}Usage:@{ub}
  GetWindowDims <stem> [DEF=DEFAULT]

    <stem> - A variable to copy the window data into.

    DEFAULT - The values returned are the default window settings, otherwise
             the data are the current dimensions of the current window.


@{b}Results:@{ub}
<stem>.x = Window's left edge.
<stem>.y = Window's top edge.
<stem>.width = Window's width.
<stem>.height = Window's height.
<stem>.cascadex = Offset to add to the default left edge of each new window.
<stem>.cascadey = Offset to add to the default top edge of each new window.

rc     - Always 0 (OK).
result - Not used.

---

@{u}@{b}SetWindowDims@{ub}@{uu}
  Change the current window's dimension, or the default settings.


@{b}Usage:@{ub}
  SetWindowDims [X=LEFTEDGE] [Y=TOPEDGE] [W=WIDTH] [H=HEIGHT]
                [CSCX=CASCADEX] [CSCY=CASCADEY] [DEF=DEFAULT]

    LEFTEDGE, TOPEDGE - Set window's position.
    WIDTH, HEIGHT - Set window's dimensions.
    CASCADEX, CASCADEY - Set the tiling offsets.
    DEFAULT - Alter the default window settings, otherwise the current window
             is moved and/or resized.
             There is no difference between the current and default CascadeX
             and CascadeY values.


@{b}Results:@{ub}
rc     - Always 0 (OK).
result - Not used.
@endnode


@node RX_WINLIST "TTManager ARexx:  GetWindowList"
@toc AREXX

@{u}@{b}GetWindowList@{ub}@{uu}
