    <stem> - A varaible to copy the window data into.

    CURRENTSCREEN - Just return info about the windows on the current screen.


@{b}Results:@{ub}
<stem>.count = Number of windows open.
<stem>.current = ID of the current window.
<stem>.<n>.name = Filename of icon in window <n>.
<stem>.<n>.id = Window <n>'s ID.
<stem>.<n>.<screen> - Name of the screen window <n> is on.
(<n> = 0 to count-1)

rc     - Always 0 (OK).
result - Not used.
@endnode


@node RX_TTMOV "TTManager ARexx:  MoveTooltype"
@toc AREXX

@{u}@{b}MoveTooltype@{ub}@{uu}
  Moves a tooltype to another position in the tooltype list.

* This command requires a TTManager window to be open.


@{b}Usage:@{ub}
  MoveTooltype [FROM <num>] TO <num>

    FROM - The tooltype to be moved.  0 = first tooltype.
           Defaults to the current tooltype.

      TO - The position to move the tooltype to.


@{b}Results:@{ub}
rc     - 5 (WARN) = No open windows.
result - Not used.


@{b}Example:@{ub}
  Beginning tooltype list:  Zero
                            One
        Current tooltype -> Two
                            Three

'MOVETOOLTYPE TO 3'

        New tooltype list:  Zero
                            One
                            Three
        Current tooltype -> Two
@endnode


@node RX_NEW "TTManager Arexx:  New, NewWindow"
@toc AREXX

@{u}@{b}New, NewWindow@{ub}@{uu}
